reviews.text: We're always skeptical of hotel restaurants, as many aren't recommended and would hardly have a chance of survival without the attached hotel. The Landing is a notable exception. The food is truly good and offers a welcome change from the usual American fare. You can even overlook the fact that the chicken cordon bleu is just formed meat. The terrace is a wonderful place to enjoy the sunset, where there's also a great selection of drinks.
Lunch here. Maddy gave great service! We would definitely come back. Exceeded expectations. Easy and plentiful parking. Blackened trout, skinny fries, asparagus, mashed potatoes - all yum.
Food was delicious. I had the lake trout. It was cooked perfectly!   Harold was our server and he did a great job!

Went for dinner and was very happy. The Landing Old fashioned was the winner for the pre-dinner drink! Scallop dinner and Whitefish dinner were both excellent! Augratin potatoes were the best we've had! Must try! Service was perfect!

We went for the Friday Fish fry and it was very good. Whitefish can be tricky to get right, and I think they did a good job. The batter was perfectly seasoned and crispy, and the tartar sauce was bright and creamy to match. I got the potato wedges as one of the sides, and they were excellent, plus you get a lot of them. We started the meal with their cheese curds, and they were very good. The batter was similar to tempura batter, which makes it light and crispy. We didn't really care for the tomato jam they were served with, so we added a side of their ranch. It is a lighter version of ranch, which cuts the richness of a fried cheese curd very well, and we really enjoyed that. We each had a blueberry spritzer to drink, and I really enjoyed it. It's made with soda water, so it isn't too sweet, but it does have a sugar rim, which adds a controllable amount of sweetness. Overall, it was a good meal and couldn't beat the outdoor seating overlooking Lake Superior.

detailedReviews.text: Beautiful views of Lake Superior, nice background music and professional staff. The specials were exceptional- we have never had such exquisitely prepared pork and salmon. The pork was so tender you did not need a knife. The salmon was beautifully seasoned- the sides were perfect. Fun drinks and the chocolate br√ªl√©e was to die for. Thanks again!

detailedReviews.text:
The food was not great, lots of commercial, premade aspects like the gravy.  The weird dipping sauce for the cheese curds was also unpleasant though the curds themselves weren't bad.

Went to get a carry out order and the waitress that helped me seemed put out that I was picking up and not dining in.  Just generally a rude vibe from her.

Don't think I'll go back.  There are way better places to eat within 30 minutes of the Landing.

detailedReviews.text: Lovely spot with great view of the bay and very tasty food. We enjoyed the roast pork and mashed potatoes, all you can eat whitefish, and personal pizza. All were generous and well seasoned. Big disappointment that they don‚Äôt offer hot tea on a winter day. I mean, how hard is to offer that‚Ä¶. about the simplest thing on earth? Please invest in a box or two of tea. Thanks.

detailedReviews.text: Tucked off the highway, easy to get to. Great menu selection, large portions. Service was friendly and efficient. The food was fresh and served hot. Prices are reasonable. Nice atmosphere, comfortable, and easy to have a conversation while eating. Definitely will come back.

detailedReviews.author: MEC M.R.
detailedReviews.text: I'm still trying to process how awful this meal was.  We ordered the tuna tartare starter and it was inedible.  The dish consisted of heavily soy sauced tuna and avocados, served with crostini.  Not appetizing at all.  The porterhouse steak for 2 was not much better. The wild rice pilaf was also inedible, as it was completely undercooked and lacking in flavor.  Uncle Ben's would have been better.  The asparagus looked and tasted  like it was microwaved. Overcooked, no seasoning, and came out with a side of butter. The steak was fine, but for $65 a bit pricey if everything else was unfit to eat.  If this expereince had an upside, it was our server, Sofie; she was on top of it and I understand none of the food prep was her fault. She was prompt and courteous. Inpsite of her excellent service, we don't have plans to ever return.

detailedReviews.author: Matt Bolen
detailedReviews.text: We went for the Friday Fish fry and it was very good. Whitefish can be tricky to get right, and I think they did a good job. The batter was perfectly seasoned and crispy, and the tartar sauce was bright and creamy to match. I got the potato wedges as one of the sides, and they were excellent, plus you get a lot of them. We started the meal with their cheese curds, and they were very good. The batter was similar to tempura batter, which makes it light and crispy. We didn't really care for the tomato jam they were served with, so we added a side of their ranch. It is a lighter version of ranch, which cuts the richness of a fried cheese curd very well, and we really enjoyed that. We each had a blueberry spritzer to drink, and I really enjoyed it. It's made with soda water, so it isn't too sweet, but it does have a sugar rim, which adds a controllable amount of sweetness. Overall, it was a good meal and couldn't beat the outdoor seating overlooking Lake Superior.

The steak was fine, the onions were missing and the rice was a pilaf goo that had about 20 grains of wild rice  . . . In northern Wisconsin which is home to real wild rice.   Wine list was limited.  We had talked about dessert but decided our options were better with Walmart cheesecake.  The Landing has a nice physical structure but don‚Äôt let that fool you.  Don‚Äôt go!!

detailedReviews.author: Diane Gordon
detailedReviews.text: On Easter Sunday (2024), my family thought for the Ist time to try the dine in. Lot of the restraunts were done with the Easter Dinner because they ran out of food. So we tried the Landing and am so glad we did. The waiter was very friendly and was on top of everything. The Easter brunch was just like as if you were at home cooking your Easter Brunch. Food was delicious!! I asked the male waiter, who is the Owner  because I would like to put in a good word for you and he said " Oh, he is right here", so we all started to laugh. The Owner was very friendly and had a smile on his face. So I told him what we thought on how the waiter was very friendly and Professional. He smiled and said Thank You. We will definitely be going back. Very Friendly and Welcoming.

detailedReviews.author: Crystal Glass
detailedReviews.text: The food was incredible. Be patient with the food as it so fresh. The drinks were incredible. Best whitefish I‚Äôve ever had.
